title: Facebook’s Free Internet Access Program in Developing Countries Provokes Backlash
text:
Facebook’s Free Internet Access Program in Developing Countries Provokes Backlash In India and Indonesia, users criticize Internet.org initiative, saying it violates the principles of net neutrality By Newley Purnell in Singapore and Newley Purnell Resty Woro Yuniar in Jakarta Sept. 24, 2015 2:33 p.m. ET 
When Muhammad Maiyagy Gery heard about a new mobile app from Facebook Inc. that provides free Internet access in his native Indonesia, he was excited.
